  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Islamic Relief USA, in collaboration with the UNHCR (United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees), is working to provide relief and humanitarian assistance to internal refugees in the Rakhine State of Myanmar.

There is an urgent need for shelter for internally displaced families and their host communities. Many now homeless people are living in community centers, churches and temporary camp sites. Islamic Relief is working with UNHCR to provide emergency shelters for more than 1,600 individuals in Sittwe, Rakhine State. These temporary family unit shelter spaces will house internally displaced persons (IDPs) until permanent housing solutions are found.</narrative>
  </description>
